.TH UPDATE-IP "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
update-ip \- Updates the IP address for motd and issue files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B update-ip
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B update-ip
is a script for updating IP address information in system MOTD (Message of the Day) and issue files. It refreshes the displayed IP address when it changes.
.PP
The script is typically run periodically or when network configuration changes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B update-ip
Update IP in system files
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/update-ip/settings.conf
User configuration file for update-ip preferences
.TP
.B /etc/motd
Message of the day file
.TP
